<br>
My question is two-fold.  I've saved about 20pp, and I was wondering what I might look to spend that on.  So far I have mostly raw silk and a survival staff.  Some type of low level weapon, or just continue to save?  Also, I was wondering how hard it is to get to the Bazaar on Sullon from Cabalis without getting pk'd over and over.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorlik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korlik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/28/02 6:19:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1911.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Monk on Sullon Zek</span><hr size=1> I think it would be kinda tough to get to the Bazaar from where you are, the nearest port up is in DL. If you wanna work on tailoring you could make cured silk armor. I think the best way for you to get to the nexus is to get a port there, but 20pp won't buy a whole lot better gear than what you have atm. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181185">Korlik Klawfist</a><BR>
